import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.boxplot(x="income", data=data)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of income across different countries?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['income', 'health']]
    sns.scatterplot(x='income', y='health', data=data)
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between income and health?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region')['population'].sum().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='region', y='population', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region').mean().reset_index()
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    sns.set_palette("husl")
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='region', y='income', data=data, ax=ax, label='income')
    sns.barplot(x='region', y='health', data=data, ax=ax, label='health')
    ax.set(xlabel='Region', ylabel='Average', title='What is the average income and health by region?')
    ax.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
